entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about your kids

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: one son grown handsome father of two

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you find it easy to be a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no it is actually very hard for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is the hardest thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not becoming angry too quickly

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is the best thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: being able to cultivate a mind love someone unconditionally

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some ways that you are different as a parent than your parents

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i went through a lot of traa as a child so as a parent i was very afraid for my child to go through that same traa tried to protect him from it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: cool how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not very good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: seems like everyday i argue with somebody about something but yesterday

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a lady tried to cut line in the grocery store and i politely told her i was in line and she did not wanna move

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: has that gotten you in trouble

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes it has because sometimes if people do not want to move then i feel it is my place to move them

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what is something you feel guilty about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hurting people physically

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you give me an example of that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: if i feel disrespected or somebody puts their hands on me i can get very ugly i do not like that about me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was pulled over by the police and they had someone with my name and they were very rude to me and i really was not happy with the way they treated me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: how to stay calm when someone has crossed over into my boundary my personal space

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how hard is that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is hard you can not live in this world without other people sometimes they just irritate the heck out of me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: being assaulted in the military is something i wish i could forget

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just that i felt helpless alone ashamed and angry that is about all i wanna go into

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see okay how old were you when you joined the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: eighteen

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: you were very young were not you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah very young

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: did you ever see combat

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did serving in the military change you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because i was assaulted and and i have a fear of people in uniform like the policemen hurting me or other military veterans hurting me when they explode or go off or have issues of ptsd

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see when was the last time that happened

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i can not remember

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what did you do after the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i worked for the federal government

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah what did you study at school

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: administration of justice

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are you still working in that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i do not work anymore

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: almost two years

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the feeling that i was always gonna be hurt that someone was out to get me i had nightmares panic attacks anxiety attacks outburts outburts of anger i was always in emotional pain and i always wanted to hit somebody

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes mostly disrespect but i feel it is disrespect of people getting too close to me or i feel in fear of them for some reason

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i can not remember the last time i had a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: what

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: irritable angry moody pissed off irrational

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: tired sick of the world angry at the world wanting to be left alone

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: sometimes i do not wanna go on

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what advice would you give to yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: do not trust anyone be careful be wary of people and what they want from you

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my son my grandchildren

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not have a a real family i do not have not seen my brothers in like twenty thirty years i only have two brothers and i do not have not seen them my mother is family i have not seen in years my father is family i have not seen in years my parents are dead my son lives in another state

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: wow some of the older people that i give care to sometimes i am a caregiver so sometimes the people that i work with older and wiser

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what would you say are some of your best qualities

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am loyal spiritual supportive kind generous
